  "text": "Pedestrian detection is a very actively researched task in the computer vision community, both in academia and industry. It has applications in many different domains, including robotics and autonomous vehicles, entertainment, and smart EuroCityPersons was released in 2018 but we include results of few older models on it as well. Dotted line marks the human performance on Caltech. Right: We show comparison between traditional single-dataset train and test evaluation on Caltech [CITATION_1] vs. cross-dataset evaluation for 3 pedestrian detectors and one general object detector (Cascade R-CNN). Methods enclosed in bounding-box are trained on CityPersons [CITATION_2] and evaluated on Caltech [CITATION_3] , while others are trained on Caltech.",
